<subSubSection id="BEFE65458554FFE809D2DC68FE144FB7" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F65B36CE8554FFE809D2DC68FE144FB7" blockId="5.[192,802,567,1234]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE809D2DC68FE2F492B" authorityName="Werner" authorityYear="1936" box="[240,451,567,590]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE809D2DC68FE2F492B" box="[240,451,567,590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Werner in 1936 from 
<collectingCountry id="8EF3765E8554FFE80819DC09FE244908" box="[315,456,598,621]" name="Mozambique" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
and has been accepted as valid by other authors (
<bibRefCitation id="92754B3F8554FFE808A9DC2BFD8A49EE" author="Vachon" box="[395,614,628,651]" firstAuthor="Vachon" page="179" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="170 - 184" refId="ref18287" refString="VACHON, M. 1940. Voyage en A. O. F. de L. Berland et J. Millot. Scorpions. V. Bull. Soc. Zool. France 65: 170 - 184." type="journal article" year="1940">Vachon, 1940: 179</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="92754B3F8554FFE80B54DC2BFF3249CF" author="Weidner" firstAuthor="Weidner" page="98" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="89 - 142" refId="ref18490" refString="WEIDNER, H. 1959. Die Entomologischen Sammlungen des Zoologischen Staatsinstituts und Zoologischen Museums Hamburg, I. Teil, Pararthropoda und Chelicerata I. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 57: 89 - 142." type="journal article" year="1959">Weidner, 1959: 98</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="92754B3F8554FFE809D2DCCCFD8449CF" author="LAMORAL, B. H. &amp; S. REYNDERS" box="[240,616,659,682]" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Natal Museum" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="489 - 576" part="22" refId="ref17245" refString="LAMORAL, B. H. &amp; S. REYNDERS 1975. A catalogue of the scorpions described from the Ethiopian Faunal Region up to December 1973. Annals of the Natal Museum, 22: 489 - 576." title="A catalogue of the scorpions described from the Ethiopian Faunal Region up to December 1973" type="journal article" year="1975">Lamoral &amp; Reynders, 1975: 498</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="92754B3F8554FFE80B58DCCCFF0749AC" author="KOVARIK, F." bookContentInfo="176 pp" journalOrPublisher="Jihlava (Czech Republic): Publishing House &quot; Madagaskar" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" refId="ref16585" refString="KOVARIK, F. 1998. Stiri [Scorpiones]. Jihlava (Czech Republic): Publishing House &quot; Madagaskar &quot;, 176 pp (in Czech)." title="Stiri [Scorpiones]" type="book" year="1998">Kovařík, 1998: 104</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="92754B3F8554FFE809D8DCEDFE1449AC" author="LOWE" box="[250,504,690,713]" firstAuthor="Fet" page="79" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="185 - 192" refId="ref17483" refString="LOWE, G. 2000. A new species of Babycurus (Scorpiones: Buthidae) from northern Oman. Entomological News, 111: 185 - 192." type="journal article" year="2000">Fet &amp; Lowe, 2000: 79</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="92754B3F8554FFE80B25DCEDFD0E49AC" author="KOVARIK, F." box="[519,738,690,713]" journalOrPublisher="Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemicae" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="235 - 265" part="64" refId="ref16615" refString="KOVARIK, F. 2000. Revision of Babycurus with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemicae, 64: 235 - 265." title="Revision of Babycurus with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones: Buthidae)" type="journal article" year="2000">Kovařík, 2000: 252</bibRefCitation>
). The first author (F.K.) recently studied the 
<typeStatus id="295F886C8554FFE80B52DC8FFD444982" box="[624,680,720,743]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">types</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="6EDF2A4B8554FFE80B98DC8FFF304863" captionStart="Figures 40–49" captionStartId="7.[192,278,1544,1568]" captionTargetBox="[213,1411,207,1507]" captionTargetId="figure-34@7.[192,1437,192,1516]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 40–49: Lychas burdoi (Simon, 1882) Figures 40, 42, 44, 48. Male paralectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (40) and ventral (42) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (44), metasoma IV–V and telson lateral (48). Figures 41, 43, 45–47, 49. Female lectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (41) and ventral (43) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (45), Distal segments of right legs III (46) and IV (47) retrolateral views, and metasoma IV and telson lateral (49). Scale bar: 10 mm (40–43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6544165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6544165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figs. 40– 49</figureCitation>
) and found that legs III and IV both bear tibial spurs (
<figureCitation id="6EDF2A4B8554FFE809EADD51FEA14840" box="[200,333,782,805]" captionStart="Figures 40–49" captionStartId="7.[192,278,1544,1568]" captionTargetBox="[213,1411,207,1507]" captionTargetId="figure-34@7.[192,1437,192,1516]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 40–49: Lychas burdoi (Simon, 1882) Figures 40, 42, 44, 48. Male paralectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (40) and ventral (42) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (44), metasoma IV–V and telson lateral (48). Figures 41, 43, 45–47, 49. Female lectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (41) and ventral (43) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (45), Distal segments of right legs III (46) and IV (47) retrolateral views, and metasoma IV and telson lateral (49). Scale bar: 10 mm (40–43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6544165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6544165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figs. 46–47</figureCitation>
). This character is diagnostic for the genus 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE809E2DD73FE3A4826" authority="C. L. Koch, 1845" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1845" box="[192,470,812,835]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Lychas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE809E2DD73FEE74826" box="[192,267,812,835]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Lychas</emphasis>
C. L. Koch, 1845
</taxonomicName>
, whereas in genera 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE80B92DD73FCCE4826" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1886" box="[688,802,812,835]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE80B92DD73FCCE4826" box="[688,802,812,835]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE809CCDD14FE684807" authority="Kovařík &amp; Lowe &amp; Šťáhlavský, 2018" authorityName="Kovařík &amp; Lowe &amp; Šťáhlavský" authorityYear="2018" box="[238,388,843,866]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Barbaracurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE809CCDD14FE684807" box="[238,388,843,866]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Barbaracurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="DFA357A78554FFE808A9DD15FE3A4807" box="[395,470,842,866]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE808A9DD15FE5F4807" bold="true" box="[395,435,842,866]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">gen</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE808E3DD15FE3C4807" bold="true" box="[449,464,842,866]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, leg III lacks tibial spurs (only present on leg IV) (e.g. 
<figureCitation id="6EDF2A4B8554FFE808E4DD35FDBB48E4" box="[454,599,874,897]" captionStart="Figures 95–106" captionStartId="14.[192,278,1788,1812]" captionTargetBox="[191,1440,191,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-16@14.[192,1439,192,1759]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figures 95–106: Barbaracurus gen. n. Figures 95–98: Barbaracurus exquisitus comb. n. Figures 95, 97. Holotype male, chelicerae, carapace and tergites I–III (95) and sternopectinal region (97). Figures 96, 98. Paratype female, chelicerae, carapace and tergites I–III (96) and sternopectinal region (98). Figures 99–106: Distal segments of right legs, retrolateral views. Figures 99–100. B. exquisitus comb. n., male holotype, legs III (99) and IV (100). Figures 101–102. B. winklerorum sp. n., male holotype, legs III (101) and IV (102). Figures 103–106. B. yemenensis sp. n., female holotype, legs I–IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6544175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6544175/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figs. 99–106</figureCitation>
). Moreover, it was found that the 
<typeStatus id="295F886C8554FFE80845DDD7FE7348FA" box="[359,415,904,927]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE808EEDDD7FD7648FA" authorityName="Werner" authorityYear="1936" box="[460,666,904,927]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE808EEDDD7FD7648FA" box="[460,666,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE80BF4DDD7FEEB48DB" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1882" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Lychas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burdoi">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE80BF4DDD7FEEB48DB" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Lychas burdoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are precisely matched in the following key characters: trichobothrial pattern, pedipalp finger dentation (
<figureCitation id="6EDF2A4B8554FFE80830DDBBFE76489E" box="[274,410,996,1019]" captionStart="Figures 40–49" captionStartId="7.[192,278,1544,1568]" captionTargetBox="[213,1411,207,1507]" captionTargetId="figure-34@7.[192,1437,192,1516]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 40–49: Lychas burdoi (Simon, 1882) Figures 40, 42, 44, 48. Male paralectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (40) and ventral (42) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (44), metasoma IV–V and telson lateral (48). Figures 41, 43, 45–47, 49. Female lectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (41) and ventral (43) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (45), Distal segments of right legs III (46) and IV (47) retrolateral views, and metasoma IV and telson lateral (49). Scale bar: 10 mm (40–43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6544165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6544165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figs. 44–45</figureCitation>
), pectinal tooth count and pectine lamellar structure, body and appendage proportions, setation, carination and sculpture of pedipalps, carapace, tergites, sternites, form of metasoma and telson (
<figureCitation id="6EDF2A4B8554FFE80BCEDA1FFEEB4F13" captionStart="Figures 40–49" captionStartId="7.[192,278,1544,1568]" captionTargetBox="[213,1411,207,1507]" captionTargetId="figure-34@7.[192,1437,192,1516]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 40–49: Lychas burdoi (Simon, 1882) Figures 40, 42, 44, 48. Male paralectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (40) and ventral (42) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (44), metasoma IV–V and telson lateral (48). Figures 41, 43, 45–47, 49. Female lectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (41) and ventral (43) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (45), Distal segments of right legs III (46) and IV (47) retrolateral views, and metasoma IV and telson lateral (49). Scale bar: 10 mm (40–43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6544165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6544165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figs. 40–49</figureCitation>
), as well as armature of chelicerae and pedipalp fingers. The inevitable conclusion is that 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE80B92DA21FE5A4FD6" authority="Werner, 1936" authorityName="Werner" authorityYear="1936" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE80B92DA21FEFE4FD6" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus ornatus</emphasis>
Werner, 1936
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="31E44D4D8554FFE80BF4DAC3FE454FB7" authority="(Simon, 1882)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1882" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Lychas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burdoi" status="syn. n.">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE80BF4DAC3FEEB4FB7" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Lychas burdoi</emphasis>
(Simon, 1882)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="DFA357A78554FFE8088DDAE5FE144FB7" box="[431,504,1210,1234]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE8088DDAE5FE3A4FB7" bold="true" box="[431,470,1210,1234]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">syn</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C490EADC8554FFE808C1DAE5FE1E4FB7" bold="true" box="[483,498,1210,1234]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
